results.overview:
At Granville T. Woods Public School 335, we are committed to fostering a vibrant and inclusive learning environment where every student can thrive academically, socially, and emotionally. Located in the heart of Brooklyn’s Crown Heights community, our school serves as a hub for curiosity, collaboration, compassion, and community.

Our vision is to create a dynamic educational space where students are engaged in high-quality learning experiences that empower them to apply knowledge to real-life situations. We believe in nurturing a passion for learning, fostering critical thinking skills, and promoting self-confidence in each student.

Our mission is to engage every student and family through hands-on learning experiences that emphasize the application of knowledge to real-world contexts. With a strong focus on family engagement and personalized instruction, we aim to build a community where all stakeholders actively contribute to the growth and development of our students.

Our core values guide our approach to education:

Curiosity: Encouraging students to explore and ask questions that deepen their understanding of the world.
Collaboration: Promoting teamwork among students, staff, and families to achieve common goals.
Compassion: Cultivating empathy and kindness in our interactions with others.
Community: Building strong connections within and beyond the school to support the well-being of all students.
Through these values, we are dedicated to preparing students for success in college, careers, and life. With a variety of programs, including our college and career readiness activities, after school programs, and workshops for parents, we are committed to providing holistic support to every child.

results.overview:
PS 376 is a school committed to academic excellence and the development of 21st-century skills through an integrated Science, Technology, Engineering, Arts, and Math (STEAM) program. We offer Dual Language English & Spanish programs and Gifted and Talented classes for grades K-5, supporting an inclusive and culturally rich curriculum.

Our students engage in authentic, inquiry-based learning that fosters critical thinking, collaboration, and exploration of real-world issues. Our science lab features a hydroponic garden, where students explore sustainable agriculture and plant science hands-on, connecting their learning to larger environmental concepts. Additionally, students develop environmental awareness and stewardship skills in our community garden on Himrod and Wilson Avenue. Our arts programming provides multiple opportunities throughout the school year for students to express themselves creatively. Through our theater program, students explore storytelling and performance, building confidence and collaboration skills. Our dance program encourages physical expression and fosters a sense of community among students as they celebrate diverse styles and cultures. Our media arts program fosters creative expression across multiple media forms, helping students develop a range of artistic skills. The STEAM club provides unique opportunities for students to compete in Minecraft coding challenges across NYC. Additionally, our soccer club offers students the chance to engage beyond the school walls by participating in tournaments around Brooklyn, building teamwork and sportsmanship.
 No additional priority is given to zoned students for the Gifted & Talented program at this school.
